# Pictrace - Photography Blog Cline Rules

## Project Overview

This is a Jekyll-based photography blog hosted on GitHub Pages. The site displays photo galleries organized by year and location, with automatic thumbnail generation via Gulp/ImageMagick.

## Project Structure

```
pictrace/
├── _config.yml          # Jekyll configuration
├── _layouts/            # Page layouts (default2.html)
├── _includes/           # Reusable components
│   ├── iterator.html    # Core iteration logic for images
│   ├── gallery.html     # Gallery container
│   ├── gallery_item.html # Individual gallery items
│   ├── popup.html       # Lightbox/popup container
│   └── popup_item.html  # Individual popup items
├── journeys/            # Location-specific journey pages (SVG maps)
├── images/              # Photo storage
│   └── {year}/          # Year directories (2024, 2025, 2026, etc.)
│       └── {index}_{Location}/  # Location directories
│           ├── fulls/   # Full-size images (1024px width)
│           └── thumbs/  # Thumbnail images (512px width)
├── gulpfile.js          # Image processing tasks
└── index.html           # Main entry point
```

## Image Organization

### Directory Naming Convention
- **Year directories**: Four-digit year (e.g., `2024`, `2025`)
- **Location directories**: `{two-digit-index}_{LocationName}` (e.g., `01_Berlin`, `36_Namibia`)
  - Index is auto-incremented per year
  - LocationName uses PascalCase without spaces
- **Subdirectories**: Always `fulls/` and `thumbs/`

### Image File Naming
- **Standard naming**: Keep original camera filenames (e.g., `DSCF0122.JPG`)
- **Custom sort ordering**: Prefix with `~{sortkey}` to override natural sort
  - Example: `~01_DSCF0122.JPG` sorts before `~02_DSCF0456.JPG`
  - Files with `~` prefix are sorted first, then files without
- **Supported formats**: JPG, JPEG, PNG (case-insensitive)

## Image Processing Workflow

### Adding New Photos
1. Place original images in the project root `images/` folder (not in year subdirectories)
2. Run `gulp resize` (or just `gulp`)
3. When prompted:
   - Enter the year (e.g., `2025`)
   - Enter the location name without index (e.g., `Paris`)
   - Optionally confirm deletion of originals after processing
4. The task automatically:
   - Creates `images/{year}/{index}_{location}/fulls/` and `thumbs/` directories
   - Resizes images to 1024px width for `fulls/`
   - Resizes images to 512px width for `thumbs/`
   - Auto-assigns the next available index for new locations

### Image Sizes
- **Full images**: 1024px width (for lightbox/popup view)
- **Thumbnails**: 512px width (for gallery grid)
- Both maintain aspect ratio

### Dependencies
- Node.js and npm
- ImageMagick (must be installed on system)
- Gulp packages defined in `package.json`

## Jekyll Configuration

### Key Config Variables (`_config.yml`)
```yaml
image_root: "images"           # Base path for images
image_fulls_loc: "fulls"       # Full-size subdirectory name
image_thumbs_loc: "thumbs"     # Thumbnail subdirectory name
baseurl: ""                    # Set to "" for local, or domain for production
```

### EXIF Display Configuration
The `exif` config defines which camera metadata to show:
- Model (camera model)
- FNumber (aperture)
- FocalLength
- ExposureTime (shutter speed)
- ISOSpeedRatings

## Liquid Templating Patterns

### Iterator Pattern
The `_includes/iterator.html` is the core component that:
1. Filters `site.static_files` for images in `fulls/` directories
2. Groups images by year (reversed for newest-first)
3. Groups by location within each year
4. Handles custom sort ordering via `~` prefix
5. Passes context to inner templates (`gallery_item.html` or `popup_item.html`)

### Key Variables in Templates
- `year.name` - The year string (e.g., "2025")
- `location.name` - Full location directory name (e.g., "36_Namibia")
- `locationName` - Location without index (e.g., "Namibia")
- `image.path` - Full path to image file
- `image.name` - Image filename

### Including Journey Pages
Location-specific content (like SVG maps) can be added by creating `journeys/{LocationName}.html`. These are automatically included in the gallery via:
```liquid
{% include_relative {{ location_hint_exists.path }} %}
```

## Journey Pages (Custom Location Content)

Journey pages in `journeys/` directory can contain:
- SVG maps with animated travel paths
- Custom CSS scoped to the map component
- JavaScript for scroll-driven animations

### SVG Map Conventions
- Use `pathId` attribute on container to reference the travel path
- Path element should have class `travel-path` for CSS animations
- Include fallback JavaScript for browsers without CSS scroll-driven animations

## HTML/CSS Patterns

### Gallery Structure
```html
<div class="gallery">
  <section class="year" id="p-{year}">
    <section class="location" id="p-{year}-{location}">
      <article class="gallery-item">
        <a href="#{popup-id}" class="image">
          <img src="{thumb-path}" loading="lazy" />
        </a>
      </article>
    </section>
  </section>
</div>
```

### ID Conventions
- Year anchors: `p-{year}` (e.g., `p-2025`)
- Location anchors: `p-{year}-{locationName}` (e.g., `p-2025-Namibia`)
- Image popup anchors: `p-{year}-{locationName}-{filename}`

## Development Workflow

### Local Development
1. Install dependencies: `npm install`
2. Ensure ImageMagick is installed
3. Run Jekyll locally: `bundle exec jekyll serve`
4. Process new images: `gulp resize`

### Deployment
- Site is deployed automatically via GitHub Pages
- Commits to main branch trigger rebuild
- No manual deployment steps required

## Code Style Guidelines

### Semantic HTML
**Emphasize semantic HTML tags throughout the project.** Use appropriate HTML5 elements to convey meaning and structure:

- **`<article>`** - Self-contained content (individual gallery items, blog posts)
- **`<section>`** - Thematic grouping of content (year groups, location groups)
- **`<header>`** - Introductory content, navigation
- **`<footer>`** - Footer content, metadata, credits
- **`<nav>`** - Navigation blocks
- **`<main>`** - Primary content of the page
- **`<figure>`** / **`<figcaption>`** - Images with captions
- **`<aside>`** - Tangentially related content
- **`<time>`** - Date/time values (with `datetime` attribute)

**Avoid generic `<div>` and `<span>` when a semantic alternative exists.** Semantic elements improve:
- Accessibility for screen readers
- SEO and content structure
- Code readability and maintainability

Example preferred structure:
```html
<main class="gallery">
  <section class="year" id="p-2025">
    <header><h2>2025</h2></header>
    <section class="location" id="p-2025-Berlin">
      <header><h3>Berlin</h3></header>
      <article class="gallery-item">
        <figure>
          <a href="#popup-id"><img src="thumb.jpg" alt="Description" loading="lazy" /></a>
          <figcaption>Optional caption</figcaption>
        </figure>
      </article>
    </section>
  </section>
</main>
```

### Liquid Templates
- Use meaningful variable names extracted from paths
- Comment complex logic with `{%- comment -%}...{%- endcomment -%}`
- Prefer `where_exp` over manual filtering
- Group related assignments together

### JavaScript
- Use vanilla JavaScript (no frameworks required)
- Check for CSS feature support before JS fallbacks
- Scope variables to avoid global namespace pollution
- Use `const` for immutable values, `let` for mutable

### CSS
- Use CSS custom properties (variables) for theming
- Prefer `var(--property)` for configurable values
- Support CSS scroll-driven animations with JS fallback

## File Modification Guidelines

### When Adding New Locations
1. Use the gulp workflow - don't manually create directories
2. Location names should be single words or PascalCase compounds
3. Avoid special characters in location names

### When Modifying Templates
- Test with multiple years and locations
- Verify both gallery view and popup/lightbox functionality
- Check responsive behavior on different screen sizes

### When Adding Journey Pages
1. Create file as `journeys/{LocationName}.html` (exact match to directory name)
2. Include self-contained CSS within `<style>` tags
3. Include self-contained JavaScript within `<script>` tags
4. Use relative positioning within the gallery grid

## Common Tasks

### Reorder Images in a Location
Rename files with `~{sortkey}` prefix:
```
~01_featured.jpg    (shows first)
~02_second.jpg      (shows second)
DSCF0123.jpg        (natural sort after ~ files)
```

### Add a New Year
Simply add images with the new year in the gulp prompt - directories are created automatically.

### Create Location-Specific Content
Create `journeys/{LocationName}.html` with custom HTML/SVG/CSS/JS.